UBS Says Man Arrested in London Is Related to Trading Loss

-- B y   E l e n a   L o g u t e n k o v a
-- 
2011-09-15T09:17:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/ubs-says-man-arrested-in-london-is-related-to-its-2-billion-trading-loss.html
UBS AG (UBSN) ,  Switzerland ’s biggest bank,
said the arrest of a 31-year-old man in central  London  announced
by the London police today is related to the company’s trading
loss.  London police said in a statement that it had made the
arrest on “suspicion of fraud by abuse of position” at 3:30
a.m. The man remains in police custody and an investigation has
been launched, the police statement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Elena Logutenkova at 
 elogutenkova@bloomberg.net  